Related to #1969.

The following should work, but Psalm doesn't take note of the `$Foo instanceof $fooClass` when `$fooClass` is generic.

```php
<?php

interface Foo {}

final class FooStorage
{
    /** @var array<class-string<Foo>, Foo> */
    private $storage = [];
  
    /**
     * @template T as Foo
     * @template-typeof T $fooClass
     * @param class-string<T> $fooClass
     * @return T|null
     */
    public function get($fooClass)
    {
        if (isset($this->storage[$fooClass])) {
            $Foo = $this->storage[$fooClass];

            if ($Foo instanceof $fooClass) {
                return $Foo;
            }
        }

        return null;
    }
}
```
Psalm output (using commit 352f18b): 
```
ERROR: InvalidReturnStatement - 22:21 - The type 'Foo' does not match the declared return type 'T as Foo|null' for FooStorage::get

ERROR: InvalidReturnType - 14:16 - The declared return type 'T|null' for FooStorage::get is incorrect, got 'null|Foo'
```

