issue.body:
# Feature request
Support enforcing key-value type relation for arrays (iterables, more broadly):

```php
class Container
{
    private $factories;

    /**
     * @template T
     * @param array<class-string<T>, callable() : T> $factories
     */
    public function __construct(array $factories)
    {
        $this->factories = $factories;
    }
}
```

_From the discussion in #2433_ 

Below, for any descendant of `Base`, `factory()` is expected to return an instance of the same class it was called on (and is flagged by Psalm if it doesn't). So where a type parameter is constrained to be `T of Base` we can assume `T::factory()` returns `T`. Thus `C::f()` should not be flagged with `InvalidReturnStatement`.

https://psalm.dev/r/1a056c3be2
```php
<?php
class Base {
  /** @return static */
  public static function factory(): self {
    return new self();
  }
}

/** 
 * @template T of Base
 * @param class-string<T> $t
 * @return T 
 */
function f(string $t) {
  return $t::factory(); // in functions it's fine
}

/** @template T of Base */
class C {
  /** @var class-string<T> */
  private string $t;

  /** @param class-string<T> $t */
  public function __construct($t) { $this->t = $t; }
  
  /** @return T */
  public function f(): Base {
    return ($this->t)::factory(); // and it should be allowed in methods just like it is for the function above
  }
}
```
**Expected**: no issues
**Actual**:
```
Psalm output (using commit 2b6831b):

ERROR: InvalidReturnStatement - 27:12 - The type 'T as Base' does not match the declared return type 'T:C as Base' for C::f

ERROR: InvalidReturnType - 25:15 - The declared return type 'T' for C::f is incorrect, got 'T'
```

