I think specifying the template at the property level might be the simplest to understand, conceptually e.g.

```
/**
 * @template T of Foo
 * @var array<class-string<T>, T>
 */
private array $map;

/**
 * @template T of Foo
 * @var array<class-string<T>, callable():T>
 */
private array $factories;
```
